nl.tno.stormcv.fetcher

Class FetchAndOperateFetcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tno.stormcv.fetcher.FetchAndOperateFetcher
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, IFetcher<CVParticle>

    public class FetchAndOperateFetcher
extends Object
implements IFetcher<CVParticle>
    A meta IFetcher that enables the use of an Operation directly within the spout. Data fetched is directly executed by the configured operation. This avoids data transfer from Spout to Bolt but is only useful when the operation can keep up with the load provided by the fetcher. A typical setup will be some Fetcher emitting Frame objects and a ISingleInputOperation that processes the Frame. Hence it is also possible to use a SequentialFrameOp. It is possible to provide a IBatchOperation if the output of the Fetcher is set to emit GroupOfFrames using the groupOfFramesOutput(...) function some Fetchers have.
    Author:
    Corne Versloot
